1 AN ACT concerning the state corporation commission; relating to energy
2 efficiency standards; authorizing the commission to make
3 recommendations regarding energy efficiency standards for residential,
4 commercial and industrial structures; amending K.S.A. 66-1227 and
5 repealing the existing section.
6
7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
8 Section 1. K.S.A. 66-1227 is hereby amended to read as follows: 66-
9 1227. (a) The international energy conservation code 2006 (IECC 2006) is
10 hereby adopted as the applicable energy efficiency standard for new
11 commercial and industrial structures in this state.
12 (b) The state corporation commission may recommend energy
13 efficiency standards for residential, commercial or industrial structures.
14 The state corporation commission has no authority to adopt or enforce
15 energy efficiency standards for residential, commercial or industrial
16 structures.
17 (c) Nothing in this section shall be construed to preclude a city or
18 county from adopting or enforcing energy efficiency standards for
19 structures within the jurisdiction of such city or county.
20 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 66-1227 is hereby repealed.
21 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
22 publication in the statute book.

